         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Melbourne botanic Garden ¶ 6/4/71. ¶ Sir ¶  ¶ In reply to your letter 1167 ¶ W. Odgers to M, 5 April 1871. ¶  ¶ I have the honor to inform you, that I have yesterday submitted an estimate of the expen...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">71.04.06a</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To William Odgers</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">Y71/4531, unit 531, VPRS 3991/P inward registered correspondence, VA 475 Chief Secretary's Office, Public Record Office, Victoria.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Melbourne botanic Garden</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">6/4/71.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Sir</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>In reply to your letter 1167<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>W. Odgers to M, 5 April 1871.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>I have the honor to inform you, that I have yesterday submitted an estimate of the expenditure for public works of the botanic Garden during 1871-1872 to the hon. the Commissioner of public works,<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Letter not found; the Estimates<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>for Public Works for year ending 30 June 1872 under 'Sundry Works, Melbourne' included £700 'For Buildings, Fencing and other Works for the Botanical<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Gardens and Reserve for Government House' (Victoria<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Parliamentary paper</seg>
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>B 3, ordered to be printed 1 August 1871, p. 42).</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>having merely hesitated to prepare the new estimates, until I knew whether the requisitions for the current half year were likely to receive the approval of the hon. the Chief Secretary. My new estimates are based on the supposition, that Sir Jam. McCulloch will be pleased to grant the various approvals, except that for the large tank.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>M to J. McCulloch, 25<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>March 1871<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(in this edition as 71-03-25c) included requisitions for works, some of which were approved<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>and notified to M in W.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Odgers to M, 6 April 1871 (in this edition as 71-04-06c).</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">I have the honor to be, Sir, your obedient servant</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller,</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Direct. botan Garden</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">W. H. Odgers Esqr<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>&amp;c &amp;c</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Undersecretary.</p>
         </div>
